  "issue_title": "Add more per-repo config fields",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\nTwo scoring behaviors are currently global with no per-repo override.\n\nFirst, **base score** is computed from the AST tokens introduced by a diff. There is no per-repo override for repos whose policy would prefer a fixed base score across all merged PRs.\n\nSecond, the **eligibility gate** (`MIN_VALID_MERGED_PRS = 5`, `MIN_CREDIBILITY = 0.80`) is a per-miner global check applied across the miner's full PR portfolio. A first-time contributor cannot earn from any repo without first building credibility on others. Some repos may want to accept one-shot submissions from miners with no prior history.\n\nThis issue adds two `RepositoryConfig` fields that, per repository, opt out of these two behaviors. Default values preserve current behavior for every existing repo. The pattern follows `label_multipliers` / `default_label_multiplier` shipped in #1027.\n\n## Constraints\n\nThe eligibility gate as written is per-miner global, not per-PR or per-repo. The deliverable below requires that PRs in repos with `eligibility_mode=False` earn reward even when the miner fails the global gate \u2014 without granting that miner reward from gated repos they also contributed to, and without otherwise changing the gate's behavior for any existing repo. The shape of that bypass is up to the implementer; the observable behavior is what matters.\n\n`fixed_base_score`, when set, must compose with the existing multiplier pipeline (label, review quality, spam, etc.) the same way a token-derived `base_score` does today. It replaces the base, not the whole score.\n\n## Required deliverables\n\n1. A `fixed_base_score: Optional[float]` field on `RepositoryConfig`, parsed from the per-repo JSON metadata, defaulting to `None` for every repo where the field is absent. When set on a repo, every PR in that repo receives that value as its base score, and all downstream multipliers continue to apply on top. Values are clamped to `[0.0, 100.0]`. When unset, scoring is byte-identical to current behavior.\n\n2. An `eligibility_mode: bool` field on `RepositoryConfig`, parsed from the per-repo JSON metadata, defaulting to `True` for every repo where the field is absent. When `False` on a repo, merged PRs in that repo earn reward for the merging miner even if the miner does not pass the global eligibility gate. When `True`, the gate applies as today. The miner's reward from `True` repos is unchanged by the presence of `False` repos in their portfolio.\n\n3. Both new fields enforced through validation at load time. `fixed_base_score` values outside `[0.0, 100.0]` are clamped into range.\n\n4. **Only** the mirror scoring path honors both fields.\n\n5. Test coverage demonstrating: load-path parsing for both fields with and without the fields present in JSON; `fixed_base_score` values outside `[0.0, 100.0]` clamp into range; that a small-diff PR in a `fixed_base_score=1.0` repo outscores a large-diff PR in a non-fixed repo with the same label multiplier; that a miner with zero merged PRs and zero credibility earns from `eligibility_mode=False` repos but not from `eligibility_mode=True` repos in the same round.\n\n6. Zero behavior change for any repo where both fields are absent from JSON. The ~450 existing repos must produce identical scores before and after this change.\n\n## Maintainer's pledge\n\nIf multiple PRs attempt to solve the issue, I will always try to merge the solution which is:\n\n- Most elegant\n- Most optimal\n- Most forward-thinking",
